n, k = map(int, input().split())
rangelist = [x for x in range(1, n + 1)]
total = sum(rangelist)
tmp1 = total // k
tmp2 = total % k
for i in range(k):
    ans = [0] * n
    if i < tmp2:
        tmp = tmp1 + 1
    else:
        tmp = tmp1
    while len(rangelist) != 0 and rangelist[-1] <= tmp:
        p = rangelist.pop()
        tmp -= p
        ans[len(rangelist)] += p
    if len(rangelist) != 0 and rangelist[-1] > tmp:
        rangelist[-1] -= tmp
        ans[len(rangelist) - 1] += tmp
    for num in ans:
        print(num, end=' ')
    print()

import math
n,k=map(int,input().split())
ALL=(n+1)*n//2
avg=ALL//k
reserve=ALL%k
L=[i for i in range(n+1)]
more=k-reserve
for i in range(k):
    need=avg
    ret=""
    index=0
    if i==more:
        need+=1
    for j in range(1,n+1):
        if not L[j] or index==need:
            ret+="0"+" "
        else:
            t=math.ceil(j/k)
            if L[j]<=t:
                if index+L[j]<=need:
                    index+=L[j]
                    ret += str(L[j]) + " "
                    L[j]=0
                else:
                    ret+=str(need-index)+" "
                    L[j]-=(need-index)
                    index = need
            else:
                if index+t<=need:
                    index+=t
                    L[j]-=t
                    ret+=str(t)+" "
                else:
                    ret+=str(need-index)+" "
                    L[j] -= (need - index)
                    index=need
    print(ret)

import math
n,k=map(int,input().split())
ALL=(n+1)*n//2
L=[i for i in range(n+1)]
ret=[[0]*n for _ in range(k)]
index=0
for j in range(1,n+1):
    t=j//k
    reserve=j%k
    for f in range(k):
        ret[f][j-1]+=t
    for f in range(reserve):
        ret[index][j-1]+=1
        index=(index+1)%k
for i in range(k):
    r=""
    for j in range(n):
        r+=str(ret[i][j])+" "
    print(r)

n,m=map(int,input().split())
t=0
ans=[]
for i in range(1,n+1):
    q=i//m
    l=[q for _ in range(m)]
    for _ in range(i%m):
        l[t%m]+=1
        t+=1
    ans.append(l)
for j in range(m):
    for i in range(n):
        print(ans[i][j],end=' ')
    print()
